devdoc.details: A simple FIFO (First In, First Out) queue for storing addresses.

dequeue().details: Dequeues the first address from the queue.

enqueue(address).details: Enqueues an address into the queue.

isEmpty().details: Checks whether the queue is empty.

peek().details: Peeks at the address at the front of the queue without removing it.

size().details: Returns the current number of elements in the queue.

@title FIFOQueueAddress
 @dev A simple FIFO (First In, First Out) queue for storing addresses.

@dev Enqueues an address into the queue.
 @param item The address to add.

 @return item The dequeued address.

@dev Peeks at the address at the front of the queue without removing it.
 @return The address at the front.

 @return True if empty, otherwise false.
